BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-031@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Building Digitally Friendly Cities: Open Source, AI and Human-Centered Data
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260623T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260623T160000
DESCRIPTION:This event brings together distinguished Nobel and Turing laureates, senior UN officials, senior leadership from leading international technical organizations, global tech leaders, and young innovators. Together, they will explore how open source technologies and AI can empower inclusive urban development – placing people at the center of digital transformation. Key discussions will cover digital resilience, AI risk management, emerging governance challenges, and the role of open source in build\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-032@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Open Source, Digital Sovereignty, and Public AI Infrastructure in Africa
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260623T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260623T160000
DESCRIPTION:This high-level session brings together the right ecosystem stakeholders for an African and inclusive conversation and agenda setting towards Africa's digital sovereignty, resilience, and transformation. It will provide a platform for building needed stakeholder support and commitment to accelerate an open, interoperable digital infrastructure. The session will co-create a short roadmap to address the critical infrastructure, resource and governance gaps\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-033@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Responsible GenAI at Scale: Open Source Commons and Governance
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260623T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260623T160000
DESCRIPTION:As generative AI rapidly transitions from experimentation to enterprise-scale deployment, the need for responsible, transparent, and governable systems has never been more urgent. This session explores how open source communities can play a foundational role in operationalizing Responsible AI at scale.In the first half, the Generative AI Commons will introduce its Responsible AI workstream and the Responsible Generative AI Framework (RGAF), a community-driven framework designed to guide the deve\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-034@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:What AI Changes for Open Source Risk and Resilience
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260623T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260623T160000
DESCRIPTION:Open source platforms underpin critical work in disaster risk management, climate resilience, and humanitarian response. Tools like DELTA, MapX, the Risk Data Library, and the Resilient Planet Data Hub depend on sustained maintenance, community contribution, and interoperable standards to function as reliable infrastructure. AI is now reshaping this landscape in contradictory ways: improving code quality, reducing maintenance burden, and enabling new modelling and analytics capabilities on one h\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-035@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Youth-Led Open Source AI for Sustainable Futures: Bridging Developed and Developing Countries
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260623T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260623T160000
DESCRIPTION:As artificial intelligence becomes a defining force in shaping economies, governance, and development pathways, disparities between developed and developing countries risk deepening. While advanced economies rapidly adopt and deploy AI systems, many regions face limited access to infrastructure, data, technical expertise, and inclusive innovation ecosystems. This growing divide threatens to reinforce existing inequalities, particularly in achieving the United Nations Sustainable Development Goal\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-036@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Open Agents
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260623T161500
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260623T170000
DESCRIPTION:This session will explore the emerging ecosystem of open AI agents and how open models, frameworks, and standards can support transparency, accountability, and innovation. Participants will discuss how open agent architectures enable developers, researchers, and public institutions to build trustworthy and adaptable AI systems. The conversation will also address governance challenges and opportunities in building an open agent ecosystem\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-037@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Closing Discussion: Openness for Digital Cooperation
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260623T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260623T180000
DESCRIPTION:This closing panel will explore how open source and open AI ecosystems can accelerate inclusive digital development and innovation. Participants will discuss policy approaches that enable openness, strengthen digital public infrastructure, and support local innovation ecosystems. The conversation will highlight how open technologies can reduce barriers to access, promote transparency, and drive sustainable digital transformation\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
