UID:evt-2026-065@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Reception: The Global Case for Open in AI: How Open Source and Open Standards Build Trust Across Borders
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260624T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260624T210000
DESCRIPTION:Vendor lock-in, lack of interoperability, and opaque AI systems are top barriers to AI adoption worldwide — particularly in markets where regulatory scrutiny is intensifying. A new wave of open tools and protocols — including MCP, ACP, and AG-UI — is reshaping how AI agents, models, and applications connect and communicate across a multi-vendor ecosystem. This panel explores how these developments and the broader open source AI community are building the foundation for transparent, globally inte\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
