UID:evt-2026-054@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Country Spotlight: Lessons from Open Source Implementation in Japan
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T130000
DESCRIPTION:Open source software (OSS) is a foundational pillar of today's digital infrastructure. Yet the ways in which countries participate in and contribute to this ecosystem vary significantly based on their unique cultures, industrial structures, and historical backgrounds. This session systematically presents the "Japan Model," detailing how Japan has engaged with open source and steadily accumulated contributions over four decades.The essence of the Japan Model lies not in centralized control, but i\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
