SUMMARY:Data Governance for the Public Good: Equity, Openness and Community Stewardship
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T130000
DESCRIPTION:This workshop explores how data governance can better serve the public good in an increasingly digital world. As governments, institutions and communities embrace digital transformation, the role of open ecosystems grounded in open source and open data has become essential to fostering innovation, transparency and inclusive development.The session focuses on a central question: how can data governance models become more equitable, participatory and responsive to the needs of the communities they\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-056@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Unlocking the Power of Open Source for Sustainable Digital Public Infrastructure: Introducing the Open Source Enablement Compass (OSEC)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T130000
DESCRIPTION:Open source software is a critical enabler of digital public infrastructure and the Sustainable Development Goals, yet its adoption and contribution remain uneven across regions. This session introduces the Open Source Enablement Compass (OSEC), a UN-led initiative designed to provide an evidence-based framework for measuring and strengthening national open source ecosystems. Developed in collaboration with UNU, RISE, and GitHub, OSEC aims to help governments benchmark progress, identify good pr\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-057@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Financing Open Source and Digital Public Goods: A Multi-Stakeholder Approach
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T130000
DESCRIPTION:As digital public goods (DPGs) and open-source solutions become central to sustainable development, the question of how to finance, sustain, and scale them remains a critical challenge. This session brings together a diverse coalition of multilateral development banks, philanthropic funds, governments, and global digital networks to explore innovative financing frameworks, new business models, and cross-institutional collaboration strategies for open-source ecosystems. Drawing on real-world expe\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
