BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-068@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:AI as a Digital Public Good: Insights from ADB’s Research
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T160000
DESCRIPTION:Artificial Intelligence (AI) can be considered a type of Digital Public Good (DPG). However, alongside its significant potential, it introduces new challenges compared to traditional DPGs. The existing DPG standard does not fully accommodate AI, as safeguarding principles - such as “privacy by design” and “do no harm”- must be rigorously enforced and elevated. At the same time, the concept of “open source”, which is central to DPGs, was originally developed for code and does not fully capture th\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-069@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Building Open Source Capacity at Scale — University OSPOs as Engines for SDG Impact
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T160000
DESCRIPTION:Over the past few years, the number of OSPOs and OSPO-like activities in universities and research institutions has grown significantly. Many of those activities are designed to help deliver the SDGs. This session is an opportunity to explore what has been done, share what is in progress, and think together about how academic open source can do more to drive real SDG impact. The session will begin with some lightning talks highlighting initiatives that show what this looks like in practice. The \nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-070@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Cities, Democracy, and Open Source
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T160000
DESCRIPTION:This session will explore the relationship between democracy and open source, with a particular focus on the role of Cities. It will examine how promoting open-source technologies can help democratise cities by enhancing transparency, auditability, and digital autonomy, while enabling more participatory and inclusive digital policies. The discussion will also address why open source is a key element in building stronger democratic systems and how cities can better engage citizens in shaping publ\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-071@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:From Policy to Practice: Establishing Government OSPOs in Low- and Middle-Income Countries
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T160000
DESCRIPTION:While the Open-Source Programme Office (OSPO) model is established in the private sector and parts of public administration in North America and Europe, its adoption in low- and middle-income country governments is only just beginning. This session brings together practitioners from Trinidad and Tobago and Kenya - two governments pioneering the OSPO model in their regions - alongside UNDP and ITU, to share what it takes to move from open-source policy to institutional practice. We will examine g\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-072@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Industry Spotlight: Open Source in the Automotive Industry
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T160000
DESCRIPTION:This Industry Spotlight session brings together leading players from the automotive industry to highlight the pivotal role of Open Source in shaping the future of global mobility. We will discuss how Open Source Program Offices (OSPOs) drive collaboration across the entire automotive supply chain, accelerating the development of software-defined vehicles. Join us to discover best practices and opportunities for leveraging Open Source to achieve sustainable development and digital transformation \nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-073@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Open Source at the United Nations
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T161500
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T170000
DESCRIPTION:Open source is increasingly becoming an important enabler of innovation, collaboration, and transparency across the United Nations system. In recent years, a growing number of UN entities have begun adopting and contributing to open source solutions to support digital transformation, improve service delivery, and foster partnerships with global communities of developers and innovators. This session will bring together representatives from different UN agencies to share their experiences in advan\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-074@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Strategic Independence Across Layers of Governance
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T171500
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260625T180000
DESCRIPTION:From cities and municipalities to regional bodies and national governments, public institutions are increasingly navigating complex digital ecosystems while seeking to maintain strategic independence in the technologies they rely on. Open source can serve as an important lever to support this objective by enabling collaboration, adaptability, and shared innovation across different levels of governance. This session will explore how open source approaches can strengthen digital capacity and strat\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
